Class SnakeSimulator

java.lang.Object
  SnakeSimulator

public class SnakeSimulator
extends java.lang.Object

The SnakeSimulator is used to determine the maximum MPRS-length song for a given set of snakes.

To run the simulation, call runSimulation() The maximum MPRS-length song can be found by calling getMaximumSong()

Version:
1.0
Author:
Niall Deasy
See Also:
runSimulation(), getMaximumSong()

Method Detail

runSimulation

public void runSimulation()
Run's the current simulation. Calculates the largest N-MPRS song for the given snakes.

Iterates through the current SnakeTree using a SnakeTree.SnakeTreeIterator in order to find the largest song. The largest song is returned through getMaximumSong().

See Also:
SnakeTree.SnakeTreeIterator, SnakeTree

printResult

public void printResult()

Print's the result of this snake simulator

Example Result:
A maximal length 1-MRPS song for this 3-snake ensemble has 6 sings:
Rod, Jane, Rod, Jane, Freddy, Freddy.
